Dar es Salaam. Journalists were yesterday challenged to promote the investment and business opportunities available in agriculture to help Tanzania to realise its dream of becoming a medium industrial economy.The Chief Executive Officer of Southern Agricultural Growth Corridor of Tanzania (SAGCOT) Mr Geoffrey Kirenga said the media stands a better chance to inform and educate people on the existing opportunities in agriculture for the country s growth and development.SAGCOT is a public-private partnership mandated to develop commercial agriculture and catalyse an agricultural transformation in Tanzania s Southern Highlands. Tanzania has plenty of agricultural potentials and opportunities compared to any of Eastern and Central African country, he said at a seminar organized by the SAGCOT.Agriculture is Tanzania s economic mainstay accounting for about 25 per cent of the Gross Domestic Product.However, the sector s growth is lagging behind others. It s growing below three per cent.